By sharing care within self and living passed the beliefs that being prideful is sometimes said to be a negative motto, I want you to rethink that perceptive by reconsidering a new conclusion that having pride leaves good fortune. The belief that you don’t need anyone to make you feel validation. By caring for yourself in a prideful manner, you are building and spreading love by existing in who you are. 
 
In honor of @Listerine and Johnson & Johnson Consumer Health’s #CAREWITHPRIDE initiative, we are here to live healthy and happy lives with joyous smiles and good reminders to self, that no matter how audacious life can be, we stand in caring for ourselves with love and kindness.
 
Speak kind to yourself and you will forever flourish and evolve.

When the holidays come around, mental health begins to decline for a lot of people. The stresses of gifting, lots of working, and lack of personal time becomes detrimental.
It is important that we are caring with pride, taking moments for ourselves and our wellbeing. Be present, and spend that quality time with your family when at all possible. In honor of @jnj & @Listerine under the #CareWithPride campaign, I had the honor to share what holidays looked like with mine.
This past year hasn’t been like any other. My brother lives in Georgia. My parents and sister live in Orlando, and I’m in Miami. This past year I took a lot of pride in quality time as much as possible. With my finances allowing me to do things I thought I’d never be capable of, I made a point to utilize that by showing my care in traveling and making those memorable moments.
✨Spreading love & care from my family to yours. ✨

Imagine being treated like a stray animal while having love shoved down your throat.
Imagine being a victim to abuse and watching your lover post a love quote, but when you express love languages, your affirmations are treated like cutthroat.
Like you haven’t paid your time with attention, now this is your third love note.
But you survived to love yourself and became the dead goat.
See that’s all just an imagination with sparks of who I am.
I found more love for myself, my fam, and all my fans on the gram.
In the end, my love shall be cherished and nourished.
My last name is Flores which makes me a florists.
I will grow a garden of flowers then call it a forest.
The type that blooms when showered with love, a sucker for love, store this seed in a storage.
Because when I expand, I build courage.
I love me.
I love you.
But if you can’t treat me like a Queen, but like a stray, then chop and screw and leave your type of love at a telescopic view.
I’ve come far enough to know I deserve real love.

Sometimes it takes 10 years to get the 1 that will change your life.
I've been single for 11 months and found beauty in meeting new people, building bonds, friendships, while keeping and losing some. 
I'm okay with all of it.
I'm also okay with the fact that some people will pretend like they are healed and/or okay, knowing they are not.
The internet is one hell of a drug. Some are addicted to the attention they receive by telling fake stories, but who will stop them? 
The ones with the energy or karma itself.
I'm okay with being alone, and being social. 
This one year of my life is changing me in the best way. The way I have responded by not responding to the sick minded, loosey goosey ass people that love my name in their mouth, gives me the freedom to sit on my treasure box with hella stories to tell. 
I'm growing and flourishing abundantly, and not a soul is competent enough to snatch that from me.
I say this to say, be patient with yourself. Love yourself so much that you can never lose yourself again. Love so hard that when the devil in human form tries to rip you apart, you don't fold but remain stable because you are grounded. You are worthy. You are fucking dope!
~Ziggy Zaddy 💙

There’s a lot of things in life we cannot explain.
Sometimes we do things that may cause pain.
We push people to edges that are slippery when it rains.
Catch them before disasters, keep calm to maintain this internal strain.
Sometimes those people are me.
My truth may not always be my truth so what do you believe?
Am I saying all facts or am I just preaching just to preach?
Why is the truth burning bridges and shake bodies when asleep?
How many times should I fail before I finally succeed?
When does the fahrenheit reach its boil before life is tarnished by degrees?
Degrees of separation cause desperation for the needs.
But there’s no excuse for my mistakes, no room for in between.
No room to chill on walls, four walls locked me in feeling hella fatigue.
So I apologize for constant slip ups.
My life doesn’t make sense, confusion with some hiccups.
Miscalculated my own abilities to add up the add ons, hold my chin up.
I want to prove there’s a better version to the truth, like owning up to my mistakes.
I’ve tarnished the beauty of love, time to repair the conception, pump on the brakes.
There’s a significance in the essence of patience when you wait.
Tell the whole truth and nothing but that.
You can subject an opinion but it won’t make it a fact.
Place truth on the table, assure the worth is flat.
Assure the truth is real and notate your patch.
Understand that people will give you their all and your job is to match.
Match the integrity.
Purify the intensity to therapy.
Don’t speak generally when truth has density.
I’m willing to change for better, creation to identity.
Putting the truth deep in my word to shape honesty.
Actualize the possibles.
No fabrication to truth be told, no break on policy.
Commonly used lies won’t be accepted through apologies.
I’m working on my truth to perfect my qualities.
I’m forever grateful.
Mad grateful.
#TheePoeticTruth #ZiggyZaddy #MadGrateful

‼️GAY CAPTION ALERT‼️
❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🖤🤎🩷🩵🤍
4th-6th grade: I admired girls.
7th grade: I love girls. I can’t tell anybody.
8th grade: first girlfriend & got cheated on lol was told by a family member to not tell my mom I was gay until I was 18. She was afraid I wouldn’t be accepted.
9th grade: No dating. 
10th grade: 2nd girlfriend while bullied for being gay (really tried to hide my identity so my mom wouldn’t find out)
11th grade: all my closest friends were graduating and the bullying continued. No girlfriend. Just sad ole baby Ziggy.
12th grade: got myself a fake boyfriend to cover up everything I’ve been hiding. He knew I was a lesbian, but supported me. If he wasn’t a guy, I’d be with him. Imagine a 6’4 fit Jamaican/Italian basketball player, singer, and guitarist. I wasn’t about to hide my gayness with a regular dude. My mom was obsessed with him. She wanted our fake relationship to last forever. 😂 (he got tired of not having a real girlfriend and slipped up getting someone pregnant) I would leave me too haha! Like sir don’t touch me.
12th grade was also the year I turned 18 and on graduation day, I invited the girl I was dating to my ceremony. My mom asked if that was my girlfriend, I said yes. 
That’s how I came out.
For years, my mom attempted to pray the gay out of me. Praying I’d marry a man. She despised my choices in who I dated for 5 years. It wasn’t for her to understand.
We didn’t talk much for almost 3 years. The love began pouring when she found out that Pulse Night Club in Orlando lost 49 people in the gay community. She knew that could’ve been me. I was out that night, at another gay club in Orlando. Since then, my mom has respected my choices, showers me with love, and I wouldn’t trade her for the world.
I am BEYOND grateful for that woman!
I am also beyond grateful that I live my life so freely and I am supported and loved immensely. 
Happy Pride Beautiful People! 
Thank you for following & supporting my journey! ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🖤🤎🩷🩵🤍
#pride🌈 #pride #lesbian #gayaf #June1st #HappyPride #androgynous #gayshit #gaymeme

Overthinking is hitting my cervix.
Head spinning like my brain cells live in a circus.
Expose these thoughts, open the curtain.
I’m writing it out, like writing a sermon.
When sense isn’t made, I’ll write it in cursive.
My patience is high, always been serving.
I got strength, who claimed nerveless?
Script my perceptions, writing in verses.
The print that I scribble has depth, but you only see surface.
Peep the weak, I peep to seek, oh so observant.
Forget all my past, living in current.
Wash up reflections, put in detergent.
They’ll judge you for you, kill you when purging.
Forget all the looks, wrap my hair in a turban.
Blab logic, make magic, then hit it with comic.
I am determined.
Breaking the silence, cutting the burdens.
I have too much to say, word spitting is urgent.
Grasp my voice, I’m not speaking in German.
Brain says left, heart says right, feelings are swerving.
Wrong path cuz I blame life on past, I’m learning.
I’ll do double the work, raised as hardworking.
Future is me, won’t always have service, no servant.
Coping ain’t in drugs, manage ain’t in bourbon.
Bounce back, bounce thoughts, leaping, I’m Kermit.
No flip flop, shot foot, no exposed toes, shot glock, no pop off, dream top, numb touch, I need a permit.
Bubbly at birth, my bubble is bursting.
So sick of training to maintain, I think I need nursing.
Change to see change, they’ll compare your all versions.
Twist it on them, show them contortions.
Bring in the rebirth, I’m blind to abortions.
Cells pick brains like fosters pick orphans.
Popping new cherries, I am a virgin.
Roaming and moving, shifting for movement, clone me a surgeon.
Full of flaws, I want spick-and-span, I’m still a person.
